		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Philada.</placeName> <date>June 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1849</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Sir<add>&#63;</add></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">It is with extreme regret that I<lb/> am constrained by circumstances to request you to discontinue<lb/> my subscription to the Occident for the present. Justice<lb/> to my known opinions as to the necessity of sustaining it<lb/> demands a remark. My <hi rend="underline">Responsibilities increase</hi><lb/> with no corresponding improvement in income. The<lb/> same &#8220;row fortune&#8221; that prescribes such narrow limits<lb/> to the sphere of usefulness of many warmly desirous of<lb/> serving their God &#38; their fellow man&#44; has ever <del>but</del> restrained<lb/> me with stringent bonds. Altho&#39; knowing<lb/> it is unusual to withdraw a subscription until arrears<lb/> are paid&#44; yet I also feel myself unwarranted in increas&#61;<lb/>ing an indebtedness from which there is no immediate prospect<lb/> of release. When I say I regret this necessity&#44;<lb/> it has no idle meaning&#44; &#38; is enhanced by the fact<lb/> of having been one of your subscribers since the issue<lb/> of the first number. Most cheerfully<lb/> will I renew the Occident at the earliest moment practi&#61;<lb/>&#61;cable&#44; and it will ever continue to have my warmest<lb/> wishes for success.</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">Your friend &#38; well wisher</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">Alfred F. Jones</persName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
